	heroObjectPosition={`center center`}
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you're a man carrying more than you let on, the Father's Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> You've learned to keep it together — to provide, to fix, to be strong — while the weight stays hidden and the question of whether you're enough never quite goes away. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free on your phone — and it reveals God as a <em>Father</em> from beginning to end. Whether you searched "Bible verses for men," "Bible verses for strength," "verses for courage," "verses for men's struggles," or "being a man of God" — the answer starts in one place: your worth was never your paycheck, your performance, or your strength. You are His son, right now, before you accomplish a single thing.`}
	keyTakeaway={`Before you are a provider, a leader, or a fixer, you are a beloved son of God — and you were never meant to carry it all alone.`}
	painsHeading={`The weight men carry silently`}
	painsIntroHtml={`If you feel exhausted, isolated, or like your worth rides on what you produce, you are not weak and you are not alone. A whole generation of men is carrying the same weight in silence — and the numbers say it out loud.`}
	painStats={[
		{ value: `15%`, label: `of men say they have no close friends at all — up fivefold since 1990 (Survey Center on American Life, 2021)` },
		{ value: `1 in 10`, label: `men experience depression or anxiety, and fewer than half seek treatment (Anxiety & Depression Association of America)` },
		{ value: `~4x`, label: `higher suicide rate among men than women in the U.S. — men account for about 80% of suicides (CDC)` },
		{ value: `40%`, label: `of men say they won't talk to anyone about their mental health, citing not wanting to be a burden (APA / Cleveland Clinic MENtion It survey)` },
		{ value: `72%`, label: `of men feel societal pressure to be the primary financial provider for their family (Pew Research Center)` },
		{ value: `1 in 4`, label: `U.S. children live without a biological father in the home, the strongest predictor of poorer outcomes (U.S. Census Bureau)` },
