		{ ref: `Psalm 23:1-3`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 23, text: `Your Father is your shepherd; you lack nothing. He lets you lie down in green pastures, He leads you beside quiet waters, He restores your soul.`, note: `You don't have to be the one holding everyone up — your Father shepherds you, and gives your soul rest.` },
		{ ref: `Matthew 11:28`, slug: `matthew`, ch: 11, text: `Come to Me, all of you who are weary and weighed down, and I will give you rest, says your Father.`, note: `The invitation is for the tired man carrying too much: bring the weight here, and finally set it down.` },
		{ ref: `Romans 8:15`, slug: `romans`, ch: 8, text: `You did not receive a spirit that makes you a slave again to fear, but the Spirit of sonship — and by Him you cry out, Abba, Father.`, note: `You're not a hired hand trying to earn your keep — you're a son who gets to call God Father.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 40:31`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 40, text: `But those who wait on your Father will renew their strength; they will rise up on wings like eagles, run and not grow weary, walk and not faint.`, note: `When you're running on empty, real strength is renewed by leaning on Him — not gritting it out alone.` },
		{ ref: `1 Corinthians 16:13`, slug: `1-corinthians`, ch: 16, text: `Be on your guard; stand firm in the faith; be courageous; be strong — and let everything you do be done in love.`, note: `Strength and courage that the Father shapes always lands as love — not hardness, not pride.` },
		{ ref: `Proverbs 3:5-6`, slug: `proverbs`, ch: 3, text: `Trust in your Father with all your heart, and do not lean on your own understanding; in all your ways acknowledge Him, and He will make your paths straight.`, note: `You don't have to have it all figured out. Trust your Father, and let Him direct what you can't see.` },
		{ ref: `Galatians 4:7`, slug: `galatians`, ch: 4, text: `So you are no longer a slave, but a son; and since you are a son, your Father has made you His heir.`, note: `Your identity isn't slave or servant or producer — it's son. And a son is family, with everything that means.` },
